DateReviewed: 2025-11-10
Description: At first, I misunderstood what this was - I thought it was an MCP server for general use, but wouldn't make changes to the far end; but it's actually a Kubernetes MCP, that allows you to get insight into your K8s cluster without worrying that the model will update your deployed workloads. It does everything you'd think, like getting pods/nodes/resources, and it doesn't depend on kubectl. Supports namespaces and all kinds of bells and whistles. Installs a bunch of different ways, including NPM and Docker image, and just needs a basic config to get going. Interesting tool.
BottomLine: Repo for a tool to use AI to inspect your running Kubernetes cluster in a read-only way
