URL reference: https://kubernetes.io/blog/2025/10/20/seven-kubernetes-pitfalls-and-how-to-avoid/
DateReviewed: 2025-11-14
Description: I kinda love this article; it's about stuff that can go wrong in Kubernetes and how to try to avoid it. After a bit of background, we dive into the meat, and it has a format - the pitfall, a bit of context, how to avoid it, and a short my reality check to give you assurance. The seven things that can bite you are - skipping resource requests/limits, using liveness and readiness probes right, relying on container logs, treating dev and prod the exact same, leaving old stuff around, diving too deep into networking stuff too soon, and finally, going too light on security and RBAC. Love the practical perspective on this.
BottomLine: Great article on common things that bite us using Kubernetes
